==Mandarin==

===Etymology===
Literally: One mountain cannot have two tigers.

===Pronunciation===
[[Pinyin]]: yī shān bù róng èr hŭ

===Phrase===
'''[[一]][[山]][[不]][[容]][[二]][[虎]]''' ([[Simplified Chinese]])

# (''idiom'') There can only be one alpha male.
# (''idiom'') This town isn't big enough for the two of us.

